
		SrcDoc 0.1 installation from sources.

1. Requirements.
2. Linux/Unix.
3. Windows.

1. Requirements.

To compile the program you will need the FPC >= 2.0 compiler, which
may be downloaded from http://www.freepascal.org, and the PascalAdt
library which may be downloaded from
https://github.com/lukaszcz/pascaladt/.

2. Linux/Unix.

Simply run ./install.sh. You will be prompted for the directory with
the include files and the binaries of the library.

3. Windows.

Should work with cygwin, but wasn't tested.
